>. At any rate, <i>Soon</i> and <i>Soane</i> (also <i>Sone</i>) appear together in the same counties and are presumably alternative pronunciations of the same name."]}]},{"name":"Steven","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant of   Stephen  , reflecting the normal pronunciation of the name in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[{"name":"Stephen","meanings":["Usual English spelling of the name of the first Christian martyr (Acts 6–7), whose feast is accordingly celebrated next after Christ's own (  26 December ). His name is derived from the Greek word <i>stephanos</i> ‘garland, crown’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Steven Somes was born about 1518, in Hardmead, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robart Somes, was 20 and his mother, Katherine, was 18. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Mrs Steven Somes."},"et":{"about 1518–":"umbes 1518–Surnud","1518–Male":"1518–Surnud","1520–Female":"1520–Surnud","1523–Female":"1523–Surnud","1525–Female":"1525–Surnud","1528–1606":"1528–1606","–Female":"Surnud","1540–1597":"1540–1597","1542–Female":"1542–Surnud","1544–Female":"1544–Surnud","1500–1557":"1500–1557","1502–1558":"1502–1558","about 1518":"umbes 1518","1558":"1558","1525":"1525","1502":"1502","1557":"1557","1523":"1523","1500":"1500","1544":"1544","1542":"1542","1597":"1597","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","about 1544":"umbes 1544","about 1542":"umbes 1542","1606":"1606","1518":"1518","about 1540":"umbes 1540","1528":"1528","of Hardmead, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hardmead, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hardmead, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hardmead, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1518–":"noin 1518–Kuollut","1518–Male":"1518–Kuollut","1520–Female":"1520–Kuollut","1523–Female":"1523–Kuollut","1525–Female":"1525–Kuollut","1528–1606":"1528–1606","–Female":"Kuollut","1540–1597":"1540–1597","1